        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 25 at 1:44PM CST by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 144 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Bull City to near Evansville. Movement was east
at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tuscaloosa, Northport, Eutaw, Holt, Moundville, Lake View, Brookwood,
Coaling, Vance, Akron, Bull City, McFarland Mall, Tuscaloosa
Amphitheater, Lake Wildwood, Knoxville, Mercedes Benz Of Alabama,
Abernant, Shelton State Community College, Bryant Denny Stadium, and
Wedgeworth.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 600 PM CST for central and
west central Alabama.</instruction>
